Luke Shambrook, 11, was sitting alone on the side of a hill in the Fraser National Park near Lake Eildon, north-east of Melbourne, on Friday .
A police helicopter hovered overhead guiding searchers to the spot and capturing dramatic video .
Luke, who suffers from dehydration and hypothermia, was found just before midday AEST on Tuesday .
His parents Tim and Rachel were reunited with Luke as he was put into an ambulance in a stretcher, with his mother giving him a kiss .